reviews.review_text: This is the second time I visited this place when I came to Goa. First time in May, I really liked everything here, food, service. But now, the quality of food is still not bad but the service has gone worse. The service is slow and you have to remind them of your order again and again and this happened when this place was not even crowded. The staff were all out front passing time and no one cared of the order to be served. Saw this happening with a couple of other customers also during my visit today.

A decent place for vegetarians to have good delicious food.
There numerous items on the menu to choose from.
There are some creative items too to choose from.
Maggi Pakoda and Kurkuri bendi were really delicious. A must try.
Shev puri, Pani Puri were good but can be improved upon further. Coconut shake and shinkanji were also tasty.
A lot of sweet options available too to choose from.
Cards, cash UPI accepted.

A recommended place to savour the delicacies.
Click helpful button if the review was helpful.
I was in search of the best Misal Pav in goa, and i found it here.. i recommend this place to every single person.. i even tried their Aloo parathas and they were very tasty too.. a must visit place
